        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(models): dedupe implicit CLI runtime aliases",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Prune implicit CLI runtime alias provider rows from `/models` provider data when the canonical provider already owns the same model.\n- Preserve explicit legacy CLI runtime refs, including configured exact refs and wildcard/provider-visible cases, so existing user configs do not disappear.\n- Preserve explicit full-catalog CLI runtime provider browsing: `/models claude-cli all` still lists `claude-cli/*` rows even when canonical `anthropic/*` rows exist.\n- Add regression coverage for duplicate alias pruning, explicit legacy preservation, canonical models routed through CLI runtime policy, and the explicit CLI provider `all` browse path.\n\nAI-assisted: yes. I reviewed the diff and understand the command/data path changed here.\n\n## Verification\n- Rebasing: refreshed the fork branch onto upstream `main` and force-pushed with lease. Latest head is `aa9f195b96fe0b647340b177709b205645df4cd3`.\n- Current PR diff is the intended three files only: `src/agents/model-runtime-aliases.ts`, `src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.ts`, and `src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.test.ts`.\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` passed.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.auto-reply-reply.config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.test.ts` passed: 1 file, 33 tests.\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.test.ts src/agents/model-runtime-aliases.ts` passed.\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD` passed.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.infra.config.ts src/infra/net/http-connect-tunnel.test.ts -t 'caps oversized CONNECT timeouts before arming the watchdog'` passed: 1 test, 10 skipped.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- Behavior or issue addressed: `/models` should not show implicit CLI runtime alias providers as duplicate provider rows when the canonical provider already owns the same model; explicit legacy CLI runtime refs and `/models <cli-provider> all` remain intentionally reachable.\n- Real environment tested: local source checkout on macOS Darwin 25.3.0 arm64, Node `v25.6.1`, pnpm `11.2.2`, isolated workspace `/tmp/openclaw-proof-85982`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: ran the actual `/models` command handler from the PR checkout with terminal sender metadata via `OPENCLAW_AUTH_STORE_READONLY=1 node --import tsx/esm -e 'import { handleModelsCommand } from \"./src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.ts\"; ...'` on head `aa9f195b96fe0b647340b177709b205645df4cd3`.\n- Evidence after fix: terminal output from the affected command-handler path on the rebased head:\n\n```text\nCOMMAND /models\nProviders:\n- anthropic (1)\n- claude-cli (1)\n\nUse: /models <provider>\nSwitch: /model <provider/model>\nEND COMMAND /models\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: the handler returns provider browse output from the real `/models` command path on the rebased branch; focused regression coverage verifies the implicit alias row is pruned when it is not an explicit legacy ref, and that `/models claude-cli all` still lists CLI rows.\n- What was not tested: I did not capture native Telegram Desktop proof. The full-catalog `/models claude-cli all` terminal proof path was too slow in this local source checkout, so I left that coverage to the focused regression test in `commands-models.test.ts`.\n\n## Compatibility / risk\n- Compatibility risk: default `/models` browse intentionally stops exposing implicit CLI runtime alias providers as separate provider rows when canonical provider rows cover the same models.\n- Preserved behavior: explicit legacy CLI runtime refs and explicit `/models <cli-provider> all` browse remain available.\n- Security/supply-chain risk: no dependencies, workflows, secrets handling, package scripts, or auth/token storage paths changed.\n\nFixes #83342\n",
